<br>
 Kegan Steelheart stood there in the great hall of Katta Castellum watching all the guests arrive and make their way to the Council Hall.<br>
It had taken much to get them all to meet with one another but he had a feeling this meeting would be a successful one.<br>
<br>
Gavin welcomed the guests as they entered the Council Hall.<br>
Lord Dirfrops and Lord Willus stood with the newly crowned Emperor to ensure his security.<br>
<br>
The guests among the Council Hall were Ambassadors from the Kingdoms Felwithe, Kaladim, Kelethin, Ak'Anon, Rivervale, Halas, Qeynos, Icewell Keep, Shar Vahl, Skyshrine, and the new outpost of Gukta.<br>
<br>
The meeting began shortly after all the guests had arrived. Gavin and his Ambassadors explained to the guests the purpose of a New Combine Empire.<br>
The purpose of the Empire was to unite the kingdoms as a acting body in times of war, and other distress. An alliance of sorts would be the main purpose of it.<br>
Each kingdom acting as one in certain issues to help the people of Norrath and Luclin.<br>
All Kingdoms would be welcome to the table of signing this treaty of allegiance to the New Combine Empire except the ones who follow one or more of the four dark paths such as fear, hate, death, and war.<br>
<br>
Until those kingdoms change their laws on that subject they would not be invited.<br>
All races will be welcome to join the Empire. This was made known to all of the guests.<br>
All professions would be welcome with a few exceptions.<br>
Necromancy, being an arcane art would only be allowed to study in the defense of other outsiders who would use the art to follow one of the four dark paths.<br>
<br>
Only a few would be selected. For the dark arts would be very hard to control among a public school.<br>
Even then some spells from the dark arts were banned, such as Sacrificial spells among others.<br>
<br>
After going over many hours of debate and controversy the meeting ended in a great success. All of the guests agreed to join the New Combine Empire and signed the treaty of allegiance.<br>
<br>
The Council of Silver Griffons had succeeded in their task. They had indeed brought together the kingdoms and rebuilt the Old Combine.<br>
<br>
<br>
